                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/429.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Reid</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 334. December 2, 4 p.m. With reference to Department’s cable 2nd instant
                    re Opium Conference. British Government approves postponement. Delay caused by
                    the Foreign Office awaiting official assent of other Departments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
